<figureCitation box="[151,279,1122,1148]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 66–69" captionStart-1="FIGURES 70–72" captionStart-2="FIGURES 73–81" captionStartId-0="16.[151,264,1679,1703]" captionStartId-1="17.[151,264,1831,1855]" captionStartId-2="18.[151,264,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1420,464,1644]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,309,1808]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,536,1819]" captionTargetId-0="figure-135@16.[151,1436,452,1655]" captionTargetId-1="figure-101@17.[151,1436,309,1808]" captionTargetId-2="figure-169@18.[151,1436,525,1819]" captionTargetPageId-0="16" captionTargetPageId-1="17" captionTargetPageId-2="18" captionText-0="FIGURES 66–69. Tiomaniella ladam gen. &amp; spec. nov. holotype male from Tioman Island. 66–68 Left male palp (66 prolateral, 67 ventral, 68 retrolateral); 69 Embolus tip, ventral. C—conductor, E—embolus, rB—retrolateral bulge of cymbium, rpP—retro-proximal projection of cymbium, RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis, S—spermophor, ST—subtegulum, acting as functional conductor, TA—tegular apophysis." captionText-1="FIGURES 70–72. Tiomaniella ladam gen. &amp; spec. nov. female paratype from Tioman Island. 70 Epigyne, ventral; 71 Vulva, dorsal; 72 Schematic course of internal duct system, dorsal. CO—copulatory opening, EF—epigynal field, EP—epigynal pock- et, FB— fusion bubbles, FD—fertilization ducts, GA—glandular appendages, SP—spermatheca." captionText-2="FIGURES 73–81. Tiomaniella ladam gen. &amp; spec. nov. holotype male (73, 75, 78, 80) and female paratype (74, 76–77, 79, 81) from Tioman Island. 73–74 Eyes, dorsal; 75–77 Claws (75 right leg I, retrolateral claw, retrolateral; 76 left palp, prolateral; 77 left leg I, retrolateral claw, retrolateral); 78–79 Left chelicera, ventral (79 escort setae not pictured); 80–81 trilobate membrane, distal metatarsus of leg I, dorsal (78 right, 79 left)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911193" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911197" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911201" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6911193/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6911197/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6911201/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 66–81</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[290,360,1122,1148]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 82–97" captionStart-1="FIGURE 98" captionStartId-0="19.[151,264,1899,1923]" captionStartId-1="20.[151,250,1436,1460]" captionTargetBox-0="[152,1435,182,1873]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,956,1413]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@19.[151,1436,181,1875]" captionTargetId-1="figure-372@20.[151,1436,956,1413]" captionTargetPageId-0="19" captionTargetPageId-1="20" captionText-0="FIGURES 82–97. Heteropodinae gen. &amp; spp. nov., habitus (dorsal and ventral, respectively). 82–85 Borniella parva gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 86–89 Menarik kecil gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 90–93 Micropoda davisae gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 94–97 Tiomaniella ladam gen. &amp; spec. nov. (82–83, 86–87, 90–91, 94–95 holotype male, 84–85, 88–89, 92–93, 96–97 female paratype)." captionText-1="FIGURE 98. Distribution of the new genera and species in Malaysia, Brunei and Papua New Guinea." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911203" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911205" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6911203/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6911205/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">94–98</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
