<subSubSection box="[151,1259,1261,1287]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1261,1611]" box="[151,1259,1261,1287]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,1261,1287]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is derived from the name of Tioman Island. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1261,1611]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1297,1323]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bertkau" authorityYear="1872" box="[404,536,1297,1323]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sparassidae</taxonomicName>
with TL &lt;7 (
<figureCitation box="[692,823,1297,1323]" captionStart="FIGURES 82–97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,182,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-19@19.[151,1436,181,1875]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 82–97. Heteropodinae gen. &amp; spp. nov., habitus (dorsal and ventral, respectively). 82–85 Borniella parva gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 86–89 Menarik kecil gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 90–93 Micropoda davisae gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 94–97 Tiomaniella ladam gen. &amp; spec. nov. (82–83, 86–87, 90–91, 94–95 holotype male, 84–85, 88–89, 92–93, 96–97 female paratype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911203/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 94–97</figureCitation>
) belonging to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1873" box="[1155,1324,1297,1323]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Heteropodinae">Heteropodinae</taxonomicName>
. Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Grall &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Grall &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,285,1333,1359]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Tiomaniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,285,1333,1359]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Tiomaniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[294,402,1333,1359]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[294,402,1333,1359]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1873" box="[821,986,1333,1359]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Heteropodinae">Heteropodinae</taxonomicName>
by the subtegular functional conductor (
<figureCitation box="[159,285,1369,1395]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–69" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1679,1703]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,464,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-135@16.[151,1436,452,1655]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 66–69. Tiomaniella ladam gen. &amp; spec. nov. holotype male from Tioman Island. 66–68 Left male palp (66 prolateral, 67 ventral, 68 retrolateral); 69 Embolus tip, ventral. C—conductor, E—embolus, rB—retrolateral bulge of cymbium, rpP—retro-proximal projection of cymbium, RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis, S—spermophor, ST—subtegulum, acting as functional conductor, TA—tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911193" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911193/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 66–67</figureCitation>
). Females may be recognised by the following combination of characters: 1. Copulatory organs situated laterally with epigynal pockets located posteriorly, with first winding of internal duct system postero-mediad, 2. Median septum not recognisable, “fusion bubbles” indicating fused seams between lateral lobes and median septum and 3. Internal duct system simple with very broad ducts leading to large spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[1141,1273,1477,1503]" captionStart="FIGURES 70–72" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1831,1855]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-101@17.[151,1436,309,1808]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 70–72. Tiomaniella ladam gen. &amp; spec. nov. female paratype from Tioman Island. 70 Epigyne, ventral; 71 Vulva, dorsal; 72 Schematic course of internal duct system, dorsal. CO—copulatory opening, EF—epigynal field, EP—epigynal pock- et, FB— fusion bubbles, FD—fertilization ducts, GA—glandular appendages, SP—spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911197/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 70–72</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
